You can&#39;t reassign a `final` variable. And you can only use effectively-`final` variables (that is, `final` variables or those that could&#39;ve been declared as such) inside of closures. So if you want to mutate a string inside of a closure, you&#39;ll need to use a mutable string type like [`StringBuilder`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/StringBuilder.html).

    final StringBuilder myStringBuilder = new StringBuilder();
    someStream.forEach(value -&gt; {
        myStringBuilder.append(value.getCode());
