    final String result = myStringBuilder.toString();

We never actually *reassign* the variable `myStringBuilder`, so it can still be `final`. But we can *mutate* it in-place. This is also more efficient than continually allocating new strings for concatenation, as `StringBuilder` will use a mutable buffer internally and save on copying.

